	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=24736'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
-Faelin-</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 8<br>
				
				Registered: 04-13-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=24736'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/wizard.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=390#M390">176</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>First off - these changes are fantastic overall. I like that you are looking to make changes or the types of changes to the game that many of the players view as long overdue. I also like the way in which you are going about it. It's apparent you want to make changes to help certian aspects of gameplay like soloing, more group compatibilty&nbsp;within the&nbsp;classes and more classes able to fill the traditionally singluar roles of the age old Warrior or Cleric only.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Second - I'm a Wizard, have been since March of 2000. I'm obviously thrilled at the Manaburn changes especially considering that the day I got the ability, was the day it was initially changed so long ago. That was a rough day! I'm grateful you all would even revisit this ability at all - as seen on the graffe.com boards or as you see it. Manaburn isn't my reason for the post though. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'd like to know if during these changes or re-envisionings for the Wizard, if you could look at a few other existing lines of spells the Wizard has currently that are "not working as intended" or as I put it, "broken and no plans to be&nbsp;fixed."</DIV>
<DIV><U></U>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><U>The Al'Kabor Targetted AoE Line.</U> I understand fully that the Pillar line was designed to replace these (or that it did more or less), but my plea here is that there would be a use for a spell line named for Al'Kabor that would actually have some use. Maybe change them to rain spells? Al'Kabor is 1 of 3 big names in game lore that is currently very active fighting the minions of Lans T'Vyl but... if the fight he puts up is anything like his spells, we might as well give up now /snicker.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><U>The Fade, Shadowstep, Yonder line.</U> A long time ago -before the newer graphics engine update namely- Wizards were told that this line of spells was broken and could not be fixed due to the geometry of a zone's floor or ground. It was stated that this line of spells would only move us in a <EM>"downhill direction"</EM> as that was the only open area available for it to place us upon mathematically. That was then. Can this be fixed to&nbsp;work as intended while we are using levitation? It's essentially our only escape in a PvP situation and a few others that most Wizards abandoned long ago because the spell was broken. Using it on a non-flat piece of ground does virtually nothing, obviously. I used it as a young Wizard and it was a very unique (although mildly dangerous) way to kite a mob or get out of a sticky situation. I'd gladly have it be mildly dangerous again, rather than unusable anywhere but a downhill ski slope. This would help Bards, Necros, Shadowknights&nbsp;and Wizards alike actually.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><U>The Glimpse, Magnify line.</U> A long time ago -before the newer graphics engine update namely- Wizards were told that this line of spells was broken and could not be fixed due to it <EM>not actually increasing the distance we were able to see</EM>, but rather just increasing the pixel size of everything. Can this spell maybe be set to view past 100% clip plane now? There's items in the game that would also benefit from this (telescopes etc) so this is more of a spell effect change request I suppose.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><U>Frenzied Devastation.</U> I realize this aa might be working 100% as intended by you. I also completely understand you&nbsp;not wanting to change the increased chance to critical hit percentage of the ability as it exists. I've been a "casual EQ player" for a long time as stated above. I've been in a guild environment that with my work and family time coming first of course, allowed me to advance as fast as I could. That means my guild and I have not yet gotten through the elemental planes, however we have done the peak of every expansion prior and are just slower to move up <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><EM>The Point:</EM> Through the 5&nbsp;years I've played, with all the raid and nonraid gear I can muster for the biggest mana pool I can get, I'm at 7676 mana, buffed and with maximum tribute and leadership aa. I have Frenzied Devastation and Prolonged Devastation maxed out (6 total levels). In a raid environment, with equipment based and buff based spell haste and mana preservation as high as my guilds equipment and buffs can go - <EM>Frenzied Devastation runs my mana bar completely empty, long before its duration ends</EM> using Thundaka the level 68 nuke, my biggest and most logical spell to use for a "Frenzy" burst damage situation.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Can we change the "increased mana per cast" cost of Frenzied Devastation?&nbsp;It appears through my rough calculations I'd need somewhere in the 8400's sized mana&nbsp;pool, to actually be able to keep casting while it was active. There are&nbsp;vastly larger&nbsp;numbers of Wizards with under 8400 mana, than those with. Changing the increased mana cost per cast while using Frenzied Devastation to a lesser amount or percentage, would make it a much more useful ability to the "average EQ player" for sure.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks for paying attention to the players, Brenlo and Co. Keep those handy dandy guild tools coming! I lub those.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Faelin Crimsoncloud</DIV>
<DIV>Grand Arcanist of Rodcet Nife</DIV>
<DIV>Guild Leader of Brew Masters "the oldest active guild in EQ" ...and paying for it!</DIV>
<DIV>www.brewmasters.org</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Faelin Crimsoncloud<br>Rodcet Nife<br>Brew Masters
							</div>
								
