<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=391#M391">180</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>what is good for the goose is good for the gander...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>i wouldnt be surprised if more mobs did start fearing although the higher you go the higher the resists you normally have.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>fear is not going to be as good of a thing as they might have intended.&nbsp; the lower level fear spells cost little to no mana so when a necro was able to effectively use fear, there was no problem in mana management.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>what a necro, or any other class, had to worry about was the path the mob was going to take when feared and how long did it take to kill the mob.&nbsp; The path it took could easily bring more adds.&nbsp; For a necro, this is not a problem with the ability to FD or the use of screaming terror and fd'ing.&nbsp; Ghetto cc'ing was also an option using a root spell.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But in the expansions, after PoP (and some of PoP) there are many more mobs in zones with larger aggro ranges.&nbsp; I for one remember, with fondness, fear kiting in cobalt scar the various wyverns or drakes.&nbsp; If the named wyvern was right next to another spawn, I would fear it first, then target the advancing wyvern who aggroed on me..&nbsp; I would run down a ways then snare and FD.&nbsp; usually no problem with the named (i didnt want the faction hit)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>removal of the fear cap will/should go both ways and prove interesting.&nbsp; Advancement of the Screaming Terror line of spells should also open up some interesting encounters.... *flex*</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>rukasak rokwyrmr</DIV>
<DIV>66 necro</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
