<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=398#M398">181</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>&nbsp;A friend of mine kept mentioning to me how it was stupid in everquest that a mob that appeared to be "quite formitable" was not meant to be soloed by most people in the game.&nbsp;I totally agree.&nbsp; There needs to be zones in everquest set aside for soloing / duoing purposes, even if nothing else to improve soloing is implimented.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Think about an instance a bit similar to kurn's tower - lots of wimpy mobs for anyone to kill, where you always get single pulls, but they might drop sort of decent drops, or wimpish augments.&nbsp; Classes like necros would DESTROY this type of zone, leading to them getting loads of xp - but who cares?&nbsp; This is the situation already in the game, but the game is balanced against the best soloers, making it hard for other classes to solo.&nbsp; The game should not be balanced against the *best*.&nbsp; A lot of the game needs to be balanced with the weakest players in mind, so they're able to feel like they're making progress without getting their butt handed to them.&nbsp; Progress oritented games need to give players options.&nbsp; If they want to solo grind in a wimpy zone for fairly modest xp and quest drops, so be it.</DIV>
<DIV>If they want to play a poor soloer with more utility in a group, so be it.&nbsp; So they'll be able to do those instances when they want to solo, but 50% slower than a necro / mage etc.&nbsp; But the point is... they COULD do it...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You could also allow the "solo-abilities" to only be used in these instances.&nbsp; The gear they drop would tend to be decent - however, quests could be added which allowed a player to gain ldon points, if they spent enough time in a solo dungeon.&nbsp; They could leave instantly, by hailing an npc.&nbsp; It would be a really nice place to wait as a lower level with your /lfg up <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>&nbsp; You WOULD NOT be able to bring any high level people in these instances with you.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>A lot of people who are still playing everquest enjoy the feeling of an extreme&nbsp;challange, with common darkblue mobs that could destroy any player solo - and I have respect for these players.&nbsp; But I think everyone could agree that the game *NEEDS* naked halflings running around... or as we call 'em newbies.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>When you log onto everquest, at any level, you need to feel that you have something to do and that if you work hard enough, you could in a solo or group situation be able to accuire just about anything in the game.&nbsp; If there needs to be more zones like the tutorial at higher levels, than so be it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I personally enjoy the solo game immensly as a beastlord, and I know other players would too, if they were able to do it with ease.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Decrease the level restrictions of spells, so that KEI or V can once against be cast on any player.&nbsp; The concern at the time was this was implimented (from my understanding) was that casters had become overpowered and it discouraged grouping.&nbsp; We have seen that this has not bourne out to be the truth.&nbsp; There are few groups in everquest at pre-60&nbsp;in part because there is no kei.&nbsp; If you know your group has KEI, you know they're going to get good xp, relative to a level 70 with C7 on.&nbsp; So you'll be more likely to group, instead of logging on your 2 or 3 box.&nbsp; You'll also be more likely to take on a rogue or someone else that doesn't have kei, because the xp will be so good, the group bonus will make up for any deficiancies.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is a natural part of the game that allows newbie characters a better ability to reach the server mean (upper levels) in a hurry.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>hrmmm... more higher levels on everquest's servers?&nbsp; More newbie pick up groups because you don't need a&nbsp;pure healer&nbsp;because you have a ranger who can heal with kei?&nbsp; Like that's a bad thing?! (at low levels)...&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>People don't play clerics are low levels in eq any more.&nbsp; they play necros because they know they'll have to solo 90% of the time.&nbsp; Put kei back in the game, and clerics will be able to solo with kei while lfg, all of the sudden you have more high level clerics, and the game becomes healthy again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>/who all rogue /who all berserker on Tholuxe and be prepared to laugh.&nbsp; Normally you'll see one or two in the game who aren't traders at the times I play.&nbsp; Yep, that's right.. on the whole server.&nbsp; I guess a lot of em go /annon <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I know a lot of people are complaining about the proposed changes, but I think in the end what we will get in Everquest is more versatility for all classes... so just be patient.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
