		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>On the topic of Berserkers:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>While it is good that you are looking into reducing endurance costs, also look into endurance regen <STRONG><EM><U>please</U></EM></STRONG>. Even though my abilities may cost less, when it is all said and done, once I'm at 20% endurance, it's a long road back up. Maybe fix the invgor spell&nbsp;lines to recover a set amount of endurance based upon level.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Another option would be to create an endurance regen spell line, similar to the clarity line, and give it to druids specifically. This would be something else to make them group desirable and fix an issue with several of the melee classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The throwing quiver is a good idea, but I would really like to see and "endless quiver' AA added.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As for our stun/snare/head crush, I would like to either have the endurance cost or the axe&nbsp;use removed. It's kinda unfair we have to double pay for our ability. Atleast make the axe requirement just a presence requirement, like a firebeettle eye for Flamelick. I rarely have loot space because I'm toting around bags full of axes and axe components. Currently, I have to have 3 different axes in use to use all of my abilities effectively. This means several stacks of each taking up large amounts of inventory. I don't think reducing the component cost would make berserkers broken in any way, but it would help them greatly in their money output and their ability to carry something else in their inventory. We'd still have to pay for axes purely for throwing, but I think having just presence is fair enough for our other abilities.</DIV>	
