		" 
			>
			I have to say that I am extreamly worried concerning most of these praposed changes. Many don't make sense, like throwing quivers for rogues, or they give me the heebee jeebees thinking about the potential problems.<br><br>Right off the bat let me say there is one thing you can do to fix pets to make then viable on raids. Remove pet knockback! That's it, that is all you have to do. Pet knockback has been the leading problem with pets on raids sense I started playing in 2000 and it hasen't changed.<br><br>Allot of the changes deal with tanks and that makes me worried. My interpritation of all of it is your going to make warriors more capable as damage dealers, for solo play, and give knights more tanking ability. I do not see why knights need more tanking ability. There good tanks as it is. So why would anyone use a warrior as a tank if they can flip a switch that turns them into damage if a knight is around? for group and solo play I can understand the changes but it hurts raiding ability for a warrior in my opinion or at the least it changes there role. I am not saying the changes are bad but I think they need more scruteny on how they will be implimented.<br><br>Another big concern of mine and one that is sure to get me flamed is the reversing of the monk nerf. The nerf was mainly to remove a major class imbalance in the high end game. One that was known for a long time in fact by the high levels. The problem is that it effected all monks and perhapes to harshely to the lower levels. I would hate to see the reversal bring back the imbalance that once existed. I would prefer monks be given more utility in there roles as damage dealers and pullers then haveing the nerf restored turning them into tanks again. I currently play a monk BTW.<br><br>The druid toggle that basicaly allows them to become one of two other classes just astounds me. I see no reason druids need that at all. Class balance is one thing but this is more like class cloaning. With this change it would be hard not to want to playa  druid, there essentialy 3 classes rolled into one at that point.<br><br>The changes to charming just make me think that many exploits will suddenly be re-introduced to the game. I am just hopefull that enough time is spent working this out to minimize the effect.<br><br>Anyway this seems like allot all at once, and im not so sure how it will work out.
