		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			My Feelings on Class Re-envisioning:<br>I feel mage changes are nothing close to "Class Re-envisioning" and I am commenting now on why I feel that way and proposing some ideas rather then after the fact.<br><br>My reasonsing as to why I feel this is not Class Re-envisioning for mages.<br><br>A. "We will be converting most, if not all, of your summons to place the items directly into the hands of the target. Of course, we will also need a new toggle that lets players turn off this ability from anyone not in their group, anyone not in their raid, or anyone at all."<br><br>I beleive this will only helps me on one spell, my invis stone, which I rarely use in the first place. Hence why I feel there is nothing Re-envisioning about that.<br><br>B. "We will be adding new pet pack spells that contain the more used summoned pet item to help relieve the tedium of summoning many different items."<br><br>Fixing a nuisance, saves me about one min in summoning. Still nothing I feel nothing re-envisioning about that.<br><br>C. "We will be fixing Turn Summoned in a way similar to how we fix Turn Undead for clerics. See the cleric section for more details."<br><br>That is nice, still I will never get this AA since I feel there is still next to nothing to use it on in the first place at my current level. Not even a useful change for me let alone re-envisioning.<br><br>D. "We want to assure pet classes that we believe you should be able to use their pets in most game play situations, including raids. We believe that pet classes do not have many problems with pets on raids at the moment, but want you to understand that we intend for you to use pets on raids and if you find that there is a problem, we will find ways to correct it."<br><br>I really don't understand this, are you saying that nothing is wrong (which I agree with) but if there might be that you will do your best to fix it? Shouldn't we be reporting issues and trying to fix or work around them weither they have to do with raiding or anything about the game regardless?<br><br>E. "We will be increasing the availability of pet focus items, particularly for the more casual players."<br><br>Ok, that is nice but I'll go into detail at the end why this has minimal use for me with regards to my current OoW pets. But this still I don't feel this as Re-envisioning, it's for me just increasing the in game drops.<br><br>F. "We will be looking into the casting time of some of your pet heals and reducing the casting time where appropriate."<br><br>OK, nice, but our heal are worthless in the first place. They are a lot of mana for a small amount healed. The only time I use pet heals is when I solo and pull more then one mob, a faster heal won't help much since I wouldn't beable to nuke in the extra time with multiple mobs around because my pet can't hold agro.<br><br>And even a 20% change will only shave off 1 sec from the casting time in the first place. Again I feel nothing "Re-envisioning" about this either.<br><br>What would be Re-envisioning for me?<br>1. Pet scaling from Foci<br>It's nice that there will be more Foci items out there for casual players. But why it theres only a 11 damage difference from the first level of foci to the last, thats averaging 2 damage per foci upgrade. Health is even more obscene, 800 hp difference from foci 1 to 5, thats 1 hit from mobs in the standard exp group.<br><br>2. An actual role besides just DPS in a group, I can think of about 5 classes that can do that better or right about on par with me and another 5 that can do some utility with some DPS.<br><br>3. The Fire pet. This has be rather useless for me for a long time. This pet needs to be given a useful purpose or or just admit there nothing that can be done and get ride of the thing so we can stop wondering why we still have it.<br><br>Idea's:<br>I think that the stance Idea for druids is a great idea it makes the group more diverse and more desireable. I would like to see the same idea implemented for mages as well as all other classes.<br><br>For example mages would have a pet stance where the mage would be forced to stand still and not do anything else but channel mana into their pet that would significantly increase the pets DPS, HP, AC, and combat regen. This would be good for those particularly magic resistant mobs out there.<br><br>And for the opposite stance something along the lines of the mage leeching off life from our pet so significantly that the pet would be paralyzed and eventually kill the pet if the stance wasn't changed, but the mage on the other hand would have better casting DPS, mana and health regen. This would be useful for time, though rare, where pets would provide little benefit or a problem with their melee in raids or groups.<br><br>I thank you in advance for reading my comments and ideas.<br><br>Malignusx<br>70 Mage of The Nameless	
