<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=407#M407">190</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><STRONG><U>Paladins</U></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><U></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I see 3 things wrong with Paladins.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1) Damage mitigation, Pallys are weak and getting weaker as content is added or upgraded.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2) Single pulling, a tank who can't single pull needs to have strong damage mitigation to survive over pulls (see 1)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3) Agro development and retention, the higher level pally is unable to develop the agro that made pallys&nbsp;famous (or even a sufficent amount to protect the damage dealers) and agro retention is long gone as well.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Sony still struggles with providing the Knight classes the ability to be a&nbsp;capable tank and not diminish the desirability of Warriors.&nbsp; I no longer play my long time "main" because it has become nearly impossible to get a group, unless I want to tank in BoT exclusively.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The DoN disciplines are "nice to haves" but are not a solution to the damage mitigation problems, this is the core of the Paladin desirability problem.&nbsp; The complete lack of a judgable and reliable single pulling mechanism leaves the Pally out in the cold, this needs to be retro addressed immediately and can not be pushed off until the release of the next expansion.&nbsp; The pre-release nerf of the DoN Pally stun spells was, to say the least, disturbing and openly displayed the lack of understanding Sony has regarding Pally issues.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I sincerely hope Sony has heard the wake up call and is going to tailor their solutions to the middle geared player and not towards the ubers as has been the exclusive case in the past.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Troth Elspeth of The Nameless, 66 Paladin&nbsp;in seemingly eternal limbo</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><U>Druids</U></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Here I know I don't speak for the rest of the Druid community, but...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I feel my Druid is a powerful character capable of filling many roles albeit in a somewhat&nbsp;inferior manner.&nbsp; I must admit pre-62 I could count the number of times I grouped with her on 1 hand and now post-64 I have gone back to my solo Druidic behaivor&nbsp;because of the inability to find a group (I know when I will find a group based on the number&nbsp;of people LFG, when that number falls below 15 I know a group invitation is imminent).&nbsp; During the times I have grouped, I have played tank (charmed pet), healer, damage dealer (dps), crowd control (CC)&nbsp;and of course provided the last resort escape for my group.&nbsp;&nbsp; In certain circumstances I have been able to overcome my inability to fulfill a traditional role with innovative ideas based on the power the Druid brings, a case in point, incapable of keeping up with healing so begin kiting:&nbsp; After generating insurmountable agro with 4 dots, on a non-summoning mob, I was able to successfully kite a mob while my group of melees and casters beat and cast on it from behind.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I think the solution you provided for Druids obtaining groups is good and will help.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Having said that, a couple of things do need fixing.&nbsp; They have been said earlier but bear repeating, provide an upgrade path to DC, provide a usable upgrade to the summoned pet (in that it can deal some damage, not a lot and doesn't need to take damage, this could potentially be done with a special pet buff usuable only on the summoned pet) and animals in almost every zone (I smell a rat).<BR></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><U></U></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Regards</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
