			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>The spell immunity change IMO would ruin the game. I am a paladin, and most of us tag with a low level resistable stun, so we&nbsp; get aggro and the mob comes to us. We can then use it later since the gem doesnt black out like it will if you try and stack Akilae and Force of Piety. You take my aggro tools I guarantee Ill take my 13 bucks a month. And so will a lot of other paladins. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Our new discipline is ok. Its not great, the difference is small at best. Id still like to see something more along the lines of Weaponshield or Furious, but I guess we'll have to take what we can get, its better than what we have had...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The un-nerfing of monks will make them viable tanks for most Time+ guilds. In the guild I am in, the monks all have over 8khp unbuffed. There AC ranges 1700-1900. Our knights hp range 8k-10k unbuffed, and our&nbsp;AC&nbsp;ranges 1900-2300. Now our monks have had no problem surpassing the "soft-cap" and they already have&nbsp;greater avoidance and the ability to block. (yeah, i know&nbsp;Knights can too with SB aa's but it costs aa's, ALL monks have block). You tell me why not use a monk to offtank? Or better yet to just tank? Same mitigation, same hp, more avoidance a TON more DPS, and they have a legitimate mitigation disc that isnt capped by damage, just duration.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Don't nerf our aggro tools.</DIV>
<DIV>Don't un-nerf monks. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Avenger Feenixx Ortega</DIV>
