			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=410#M410">193</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<P><STRONG>Rangers</STRONG></P>
<P>Rangers are good at many things and when all the parts add up properly, theyre a class that is in heavy demand.&nbsp; Our feeling is that the parts are not adding up properly in the current game.&nbsp; We are still digesting all of the DPS numbers and stats but in the meantime we identified a couple of things we can increase in the short term.</P>
<P>a.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We will be improving the damage you do through spells.</P>
<P>b.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We will be boosting your healing ability, particularly at the top end of the game.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Looks like a DPS boost to melee, innate triple attack, or new melee disiplines are not in the near future. At least they are looking at numbers, which is better than a poke in the eye with a sharp stick.&nbsp;&nbsp; Due to the archery detour back with PoP, Rangers really have fallen behind other melee classes in terms of melle upgrades, disiplines, ect which effects melee DPS because the focus for a time was increasing Archery DPS.&nbsp; I dont disagree that a Ranger that wants to do top-end DPS should have the same risks that Rouges and Monks are exposed too, but Ranger melee needs to be beefed up a bit.&nbsp; Zero sense in having a Ranger if the Pallys and Warriors are doing the same DPS... you would be better off with the plate classes.&nbsp; I am happy SOE is moving Rangers back to melee... I am a Ranger not an Archer.<BR><BR><STRONG>Would much prefer to see skill caps like DODGE, PARRY, and RIPOSTE increased to Rouge level... that alone would help tanking ability/surviveability/utiliy much more than the trivial casting damage increases we are likely to see... </STRONG>there is now reason IMHO, that&nbsp; a Damage specialist class like rouges should have better defensive skill caps than a Generalist class like Rangers.&nbsp; Both are chain classes, but the damage specialist class has higher defensive caps than the generalist Ranger.&nbsp; Seems a little incongruous to me.&nbsp; I am not saying the rouges should be penalized because of there High Damage specialty, but Rangers as another chain class, emergency tank, emergency CC should at least have the same defensive skill caps as rouges.&nbsp; Especially since Rangers are being re-directed at teh higher end back into melee.<BR><BR>Our high end nukes would really need to increase about 50% in power to be truely usefull.... somewhere close to the Druids 65 Winter Frost spell 1550 Dam.... otherwise its a waste of time. The 69 Druid Nuke Solstice Strike does 1926 damage, while our top non-ancient 70 rune is currently 963 cold (69) and 842 fire ( 68 ). The typical Ranger shooting with all archery AAs during the 3.5 cast time of both those spells should be doing around&nbsp;800-900 damage... not really worth casting unless you get a crit which for me with SCF3 is only 10% chance... again not worth giving up a solid steam of damage especially considering resist mitigation of spell damage higher level mobs seem to have with more frequency.&nbsp;&nbsp;TIME/GOD geared/weaponed melee would be&nbsp;doing more damage and thus&nbsp;giving up even more casting periodically than just straight melee.</P>
<P><BR><BR>Would personally prefer us to get signicant boosts in healing than Nukeing. Currently our best heal base is 680. Healing Adept 3 (12AAs)increases this 10% to 748. Advanced Healing adept (12AAs) increases healing to 809. Healing Adept Mastery (18AA 3,6,9?) increases healing <SPAN></SPAN>.<BR><BR>The level 60 Druid heal Natures Touch is 978 base. Which seems to me a a reasonable place compared to our parent class to raise base healing too... Druid level 60...978hps. Hardly stepping on the parrent classes healing hegemony, but a decent base for a hybrid class. The level 68 Druid heal Chlorotrope by comparison does 2420hps base <STRONG>with&nbsp;NO AAs</STRONG>. At a base of the 978 level 60 Druid heal our AA heals would become somewhat more usefull:<BR>Healing Adept3..................... 1075<BR>Advanced Healing adept........1163<BR>Healing Adept Mastery...........1251<BR><BR>Still nothing close to what a Druid can heal with the level 68 spell <U>without</U> any healing AAs but certainly more in line with the content level level 70 groups/raids now face. A 1K-1.2K heal would make a Ranger a usefull spot healer for casting classes in a Raid situations, and spam healer for the MT at initial point of contact with named mobs till the CH rot is up and runnning smoothly. I still spam heal my dinky 680 heal, but it doesnt have much of a impact unless a lot of hybrids are spam healing as well. But near 1K healing now spam healing the MT has some real power till the CH rot gets established/attack is called.<BR><BR><BR>Just some thoughts.... needed a break from work. I hate tax time.<BR></P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>03-16-2005</span> <span class=time_text>12:10 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_rating_cell" valign=bottom nowrap 
			
