<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=411#M411">194</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Your Reinvisionment needs to be reinvisioned.You are trying yet again to make SK's and Pallies as main line tanks simply because they whined that they can not tank like a warrior - someone needs to let them know they arent supposed to.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;Rangers are having their nukes upgraded?Doing massive damage with a ranged weapon is not enough that now they need nukes to be able to solo on par with bards.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Monks again think they are tanks and needs their AC adjusted so they stay on par with warriors.Look back through real history and see just how many monks actually used armor like the monks in EQ are able to.None - the Monks in EQ should be glad they are able to wear armor at all - and they were never designed to be tanks,again a class that was mis informed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Battle druids?Now they can get an increase in their damage potential or their healing depending on the role they pursue.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Better healing for shammies,rangers,and beastlords?Now they get to fill in the role of healers for groups?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Necros need better spells to help them solo?They are on par with the beloved bards that soe so fawns over in getting things handed to them,making their class more and more self sufficient.They can solo mobs in OoW like no other class,all the while keeping a low profile so they dont have the nerf bat raised in their direction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Bards - ahhhh the wonderful magical Bard - being able to play complex instruments to make music while at a dead run in full plate armor........... Now this is something I want to see Willie Nelson do,because apparently there was never a question raised that a Bard can run as fast as a cheetah while playing a lute,madolin,etc.,while wearing heavy constraining armor.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;And finally the enchanter - my class of choice of course nerfed yet once again.I am currently lvl 69,252 aa's,and am about to leave EQ for something else simply because you have castrated this class beyond belief.Enchanters have been passed over again and again on any form of upgrade and we are the laughing stock of EQ when the words class balance appears.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; You nerfed charm to literally make it useless in OoW,who wants to take a chance charming a mob that has around 20% of its dps potential while charmed only to unleash its full fury on the chanter and his party when charm breaks? The reward vs the risk has made charm useless.Now as a proposed change,you want to make this effective across all zones rather than just OoW,effectively lowering our usefullness even further.The lowering of a mobs DPS while charmed is something that should only have come about if we were given a FIXED DURATION charm.Our charms are subject to break within one tic ( unlike a bards) and it takes us time to attempt a recharm which can EASILY lead to a group wipe let alone while soloing.Why werent we given something that would leave the mob temporarily stunned on a charm break,a short period of time where the mob trys to figure out what it was doing while we attempt to recast?Why was a fixed duration charm never considered?Why hasnt Dire Charm been upgraded,giving us the ability to DC mobs higher than lvl 46 though the use of AA's upgrading?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; Charm is the not the only problem with chanters,for instance why have we been overlooked on slows since Kunark?We should have a low resist 3 second slow just like shammies and beastlords.Why hasnt Tashed been upgraded ? Our last was lvl 61 and for only 48 points - why not a lvl 70 version for 75-100?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; Nukes? We have some of the weakest nukes available and now rangers may very well be able to out nuke chanters in addition to scoring their 1-2k critical hits with a bow.Why not give us a 2-3k nuke to make us minimally effective on raids?And not a spell that requires a 72 member raid force to get.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Mezz's? How about a low resist/no resist mezz that would actually hit once in a while instead of us getting 4-5 resists on a blue conned mob before it sticks?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Effective Illusions? How many people at SOE can look out the window and instantly tell who on the street below is a muslim,**SMURF**,christian,or atheist? Why is it that EVERY npc across norrath has this ability,yet the player characters themselves do not?Upgrade the illusions,including spells like NDT and Boon to scale up in effectiveness based on the level of the caster.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Mana regen? Why are we one of the only classes to have NEVER recieved their own personal line of mana regen spells like clerics,wizzies,beastlords,druids,etc,that stack with the current regen spells we cast?Beastlord spells can offer a small degree of mana regen,as can druid hp buffs,but it is rare to get all these classes together for a group.Wizzies and mages have their own form of mana regen that stacks with KEI / VoC,just like clerics,yet we most of the time depend on our own singular buff.An inherent mana regen of 1 point for every 10 levels of the chanter is something that would be appreciated.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;&nbsp; If we have to endure getting splattered across the pavement by the mobs we try to charm,then why dont we have some form of higher damage mitigation that would possibly keep us alive a little longer?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; DoTs? The ones we have are a joke,our best doing 94 a tic compared to ones that do 4-5-600 per tic from other classes(not to mention they have resist modifiers to make them stick).</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp; Reinvision your reinvisionment plans guys because you just slapped many classes in the face again,not to mention chanters who are still reeling from the insult you handed us when OoW was released.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
