<DIV>"Your Reinvisionment needs to be reinvisioned.You are trying yet again to make SK's and Pallies as main line tanks simply because they whined that they can not tank like a warrior - someone needs to let them know they arent supposed to."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Rofl, I love that. "Your reinvisionment needs to be reninvisioned." That's hot. XD Now... Why aren't SK's and Pallys supposed to tank like wars? -Cough- This is class balancing here, we're supposed to be balancing our classes out. Now let's put it this way... When main tanking a group you're supposed to be able to use a War, Pally or SK, all those classes should be well more equipped to do it than any other. Sadly every class in the game can pull aggro from them if they try and still do when they're not trying so aggro is a problem. Now, why should warriors get to be better tanks than the other two? Just because they have beneficial spells? I don't think so. I've played all three classes, I prefer to main tank over anything else.&nbsp;I feel they should all get equivalent and much more HP (Maybe AC too but HP has always seemed better to me) than the other classes. But whereas Pallys get decent group heals and stuns and roots for aggro and flexability (so-so, those could use some work, I feel they should have something beneficial aside from stuns for aggro) and SK's get snare/DoTs, nukes, straight hate nukes, mana and group heals (Pretty pimp class and I can use mine for DPS and&nbsp;mana battery in group as much as main tanking plus great flexability for a hunting situation/trying to take down one roaming mob) Warriors don't get a lot. To balance these classes they should all get great HP (much more than any other classes to move them a step ahead, forget all this monk AC nerfing stuff, if you raise their base HP up from 2500-3000 to 5000-6000 you move them a good and well deserved step ahead), good skills, good AA's for their tanking class (Not terribly unbalanced at the moment except for the horrible base HP and needing high end guilds to take really strong mobs and getting really good loot to make your char uber instead of just being able to make them good on your own or through XP)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Basically, to even them out, warriors should get some flexability skills. Such as Berserkers, they should also get some skills to snare the mob like a leg strike or they should get an ability to increase their running speed so they can escape any mobs if they're running solo and get some nasty aggro, they shouldn't have to die. SK can FD, pally can root and run away, Warriors are left to get owned from behind while hobbling. Sux0rz. Warriors should also get something beneficial to the group. Such as&nbsp;bard songs, they could have a battle cry. Increasing group damage output(atk)/haste/durability/hp(resolve? -Shrug- A good leader can strengthen his troops) Maybe even AA's to do some of this stuff (such as leader AA's but the war gets them when he groups with people, such as bravery or cunning AA's to increase group HP or AC or some-such) There's no reason they shouldn't get some beneficial things as well, in fact I think it's quite unbalanced that they don't get fun things, playing a warrior can be SO tedious. Also there's no reason to not&nbsp;increase SK and Pally abilities to take damage and fight well. Just my two cents, if you're gonna make the classes balance make them balance. ;p Even when I write this it seems to me like it's just making them all exactly the same but you guys can put a spin on it and make things work right I'm sure. I'm just trying to give you some ideas. ;p Shouldn't we be getting paychecks or something for doing this job? XD</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Also as for my added comment when I broke my paragraphs up on page 3 I was just messing around and yes, I myself thought it was funny I was calling him a newb when I was at 2posts with Newbie right under my name. XD I'm a pretty easy going guy and I was just playin'. ;p I broke this one up for you guys. Rofl.</DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
