			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=3398'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/enchanter.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=415#M415">196</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>On the Enchanter changes:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I really like the idea of less Tash hate and buff effects built into the charm spell line.&nbsp; I do however have some concernes that i'd like to share:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)&nbsp; I hope that the buffs attatched to the charm spell will be made worthwhile.&nbsp; In the past when changes of a similar nature have been implimented they have not been used by many players due to them being too insignificant to really be worth using.&nbsp; An example of this would be Dire Charm.&nbsp; I rarely used dire charm unless I just didn't want to worry about a pet breaking but still wanted some solid dps (more than animation).&nbsp; A regular charm pet was simply more practical, the damage output of the charm pet vastly outweighed the damage output of the Dire Charm pet so much that the benefit of the pet not breaking just wasn't enough when compared to damage output.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2)&nbsp; I'm not really sure that putting buffs on the charm spell will be all that balancing.&nbsp; From my perspective having charm break and a hasted pet coming after you isn't really the biggest problem with charm now.&nbsp; With enough AA and strategy a good enchanter can protect himself during the recharm process.&nbsp; I'm not even worried about healing the pet, all you have to do is break charm, mez, mem blur and watch the mob regen at 20-40% a tick every once in a while.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My main concern is the damage output of charmed pets.&nbsp; That is what is making charm so undesireable to me right now,&nbsp; the charm pets just don't do enough damage to be worth the trouble anymore.&nbsp; An example:&nbsp; When the OoW expansion came out, I got interested in Harbinger's Spire.&nbsp; From what I had heard about it, it sounded like a good place to farm items to sell and make some good money off of (like veksar of kunark used to be).&nbsp; So a couple necromancer friends and I went down one day to kill stuff and see what we could find.&nbsp; I decided to get a charm pet because the mobs there had too much hp for my animation and I to do efficiently.&nbsp; Unfortunately my charm pet didn't do much better, the trash fights took me about 3 - 4 minutes each even with Speed of Salik on my pet and there were frequent charm breaks with 320charisma and total domination 3.&nbsp; Also because the fights were lasting so long my pet's hp was going down quickly even with the&nbsp;mobs i pulled slowed.&nbsp; Meanwhile my necromancer friends were burning trash mobs left and right and they were able to invis to&nbsp;and single pull the place holder mobs.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My point is that having a charm pet that hits for full damage isn't really all that unbalancing.&nbsp; Some of the main reasons for me are:&nbsp; 1)&nbsp; Mobs break often even with high charisma and the total domination AA 2)&nbsp; Even when a charm lasts for full duration the max duration is only 7 mins and 36 seconds&nbsp; 3)&nbsp; The high end charm spells cost 700+ mana to cast without focus effects which can really suck for enchanters without maxed mana regeneration, enormous mana pools, or mana regen clicky items. 4)&nbsp; Charm pets are really the only form of dps granted to enchanters right now.&nbsp; We get a nuke and a few dots but their dps is next to nothing when pitted against mobs with 10,000 hp or more (which seems to be fairly common nowadays).&nbsp; Also these nukes are fairly mana intensive, especially when charming.&nbsp; 5)&nbsp; charm takes up a spell gem slot indefinately,&nbsp; pet classes get to summon their pet and then use the gem slot for another spell.&nbsp; 6)&nbsp; We can't invis when using a charm pet,&nbsp; this doesn't seem like much at first but can be a very large burden in some situations.&nbsp; 7)&nbsp; We can't afk when using a charm pet,&nbsp; this also doesn't seem like much but sometimes we really need to afk for one reason or another and we can't do that without completely losing our charm pet.&nbsp; or being stupid and hoping the pet won't break and kick our butts while we're away ^_^.&nbsp; It is for these reasons, and others that I haven't thought of, that I feel that it is only fair to allow charm pets to be extra extra powerful; because they are so much more trouble than a regular pet and the gap should be substantial.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That said, I do realize that enchanters were not really ment to be a pet or dps class.&nbsp; But I also don't think it's fair to write any form of enchanter dps off as unbalancing and nerf it to hell either.&nbsp; Without any kind of real dps enchanters have no good way of making money because they are limited to what they can get from exp groups and raids (contrary to popular belief, at least on my server, selling KEI is not a good way to make solid money anymore, but that's another story) and for the new DoN expansion we need (or at least I need, there are a lot of AA skills and abilities I haven't achieved yet) groups or a partner&nbsp;to do even the solo missions efficiently.&nbsp; I've got some ideas for changes to be maded that I feel would be beneficial:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>1)&nbsp; Remove the charm damage nerf:&nbsp; This is the most obvious idea of course because&nbsp;the damage nerf&nbsp;is the most crippling to our damage ability.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2)&nbsp; Increase the duration of charm spells and lower mana cost:&nbsp; This would be beneficial for obvious reasons and, if nothing else, it'd be in character ^_^.&nbsp; Honestly, what kind of enchanter that has reached the esteemed rank of level 70 (9 levels above the guild masters in the cities) would not be able to hold a creature under his/her influence for an extended amount of time.&nbsp; And for that matter what kind of manipulation requires uddles of mana?&nbsp; People in RL do it all the time ^_^.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>3)&nbsp; Provide charm pet focus effects:&nbsp; control the strength of an enchanter's charm pet through itemization and aa.&nbsp; A high end enchanter would be able to kill more efficiently than a common enchanter with a charm pet, which in all honesty seems very fair to me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>4)&nbsp; Give enchanters more dps in the form of spells:&nbsp; this is the one that I really don't like that much;&nbsp; we'd just be necromancers with universal slow, mez and a charm pet instead of a summoned pet.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Please consider some of these, I'm sure i'm not the only one that would love to see a couple of my suggestions go live.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
