<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=416#M416">199</a> of 829
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1193 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<HR>

<DIV>"All spells will check for immunity before they are cast.&nbsp; So if the target is immune, the spell will not generate aggro for the caster."</DIV>
<DIV>You realize that will manifest as a nerf to paladins?
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Stopcast:</DIV>
<DIV>I have an idea for the fear associated with this ability that would be very useful for some casters yet possibly detrimental to others, and while the suggestion may be thrown out and shrugged off, or even missed, but&nbsp;I just wanted to get it out.</DIV>
<DIV>Make an toggle button in the option window (much like the autostand autoduck etc buttons that effect game play) make the button called 'autostop-cast' ? and you can turn it off in the case of a paladin. I hope that SoE 'does' impliment this, and even if they do not take my suggestion to heart the&nbsp;first&nbsp;round, I suspect that&nbsp;enough people will be disturbed by the unintentional nerf that they would 'have' to create a fix like or similar to this =)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Clerics:</DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV>
<DIV>Clerics aren't 'jealously resisting' they are defending the ONE reason they get groups. Admitedly its a very big reason, but if shamans and druids can match them, and keep the shaman and druid other skills, then clerics will be obselete</DIV>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Upgrade to the complete heal spell,&nbsp;as druids gain better and better heals clerics become nervous about being passed in potential grouping ability by the druids,&nbsp;Maybe make&nbsp;Improved Complete Heal (10k) and Greater&nbsp;Complete heal (12k) and scale thier mana costs up, 400 mana used in the 7.5k heal so&nbsp;500-550 and 600-650 mana sound reasonable to me... continue with being unable to focus these spells and advance them. I would consider this fair clerics, I think clerics should retain thier ability to be the top and foremost healers. Especially due to thier solo ability being very limited compared to druids and shamans, (and druids/shamans are offset by having lowered healing power)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druids:</DIV>
<DIV>The proposed/posted ideas, are ... scary to me. While druids seemed to have liked these ideas, I feel that this&nbsp;'could'&nbsp;possibly be&nbsp;giving them a 'huge' bonus advantage, I hope the Developers are especially careful with this. There are many ideas and suggestions I, (or anyone for that matter) could make, but honestly it 'is' very difficult to please (while keeping in balance)&nbsp;a class that was meant to be a balance of all, master of none.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wizards:</DIV>
<DIV>Can you all say Woot? Manaburn being changed to be situationally useful for exceptionally large targets. I myself cant wait to see the specific final changes on this. And have been waiting quite some time to see changes like these.</DIV>
<DIV>I honestly would have liked to see the snare line that was given to druids and rangers stretch over to the wizards, we havnt had a snare upgrade for quite a while, and I am tired of snaring a specific target and the AoE portion catches either something that shouldnt be snared etc.</DIV>
<DIV>I could go on with the changes I'd like to see for wizards, but as a class that is what&nbsp;I call 'showy' (almost everyone see's those 8k crits, but we are still outdps'd by many others in parsed log files) 95% of what we do is dps, but, Like SoE said, until thier numbercrunching is done on thier side they cant really address these issues.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hopefully my ideas can be put to thought or use for the purpose of helping <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></DIV></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
